metadata.name: I Wear My Dreams
metadata.description:
I wear my dreams and tread upon the verdant path,  
Carrying abundance in the folds of my sleeves,  
Nurturing them to ripen into fruitful aftermath. 
I safeguard my home, a haven to unfold. 
My veins morph into roots as I breathe,  
A balm of self-love for wounds to imbibe,  
I am the healing, the cure, and the reprieve,  
A medicine for my soul to thrive.
